n  - `requirements_drafting`: Interactive requirements gathering with QA cycles\n  - `automation_runtime`: Daemon task management, leases, and worker orchestration\n  - `conformance_spec`: Placeholder for conformance test infrastructure\n\n- **3 Adapter Layers**:\n  - `FileSystem (fs.rs)`: All persistence (projects, runs, journals, artifacts, daemon tasks)\n  - `StubBackendAdapter`: Deterministic testing mock with failure injection\n  - `WorktreeAdapter`: Git worktree operations for daemon task isolation\n\n### CLI COMMANDS IMPLEMENTED\n\n**Fully Implemented:**\n1. **`init`** - Initializes v1 workspace with required directories\n2. **`flow`** - Lists built-in flow presets and displays flow details\n3. **`config`** - Show/get/set/edit workspace configuration\n4. **`project`** - Create, select, list, show, delete projects\n5. **`requirements`** - Draft/quick requirements, show status, answer interactive questions\n6. **`run`** - Start/resume/status/history/tail runs; processes full workflow stages\n7. **`daemon`** - Start (with single-iteration support), status, abort, retry, reconcile daemon tasks\n\n**NOT Yet Implemented:**\n- **`conformance`** - List and run conformance tests (returns `NotYetImplemented` error)\n- **`run rollback`** - Subcommand stub exists but not implemented (returns `NotYetImplemented` error)\n\n### WORKFLOW ENGINE CAPABILITIES\n\n**Flow Presets (all 4 supported):**\n1. **Standard** (8 stages): PromptReview → Planning → Implementation → QA → Review → CompletionPanel → AcceptanceQA → FinalReview\n2. **QuickDev** (4 stages): PlanAndImplement → Review → ApplyFixes → FinalReview\n3. **DocsChange** (4 stages): DocsPlan → DocsUpdate → DocsValidation → Review\n4. **CiImprovement** (4 stages): CiPlan → CiUpdate → CiValidation → Review\n\n**Engine Features:**\n- Full end-to-end execution with stage contract validation\n- Schema, domain, and rendering contract validation pipelines\n- Retry policies for transient failures with configurable cycle limits\n- Completion rounds for refinement loops\n- Amendment queue for in-flight modifications\n- Session reuse support (when backend permits)\n- Cancellation token support\n- Resume-from-failed semantics with cycle/attempt tracking\n- QA review outcome handling with remediation trigger stages\n- Late-stage completion panels with approval gates\n\n**16 Total Stage Types:**\n- Standard: PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview\n- QuickDev: PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes (with Review, FinalReview shared)\n- DocsChange: DocsPlan, DocsUpdate, DocsValidation (with Review shared)\n- CiImprovement: CiPlan, CiUpdate, CiValidation (with Review shared)\n\n### PERSISTENCE & DATA MODELS\n\n**Project Run Record:**\n- Canonical project record (project.toml) with metadata and flow definition\n- Run snapshots tracking status (NotStarted, Running, Paused, Failed, Completed)\n- NDJSON journal with events (run_started, stage_entered, stage_completed, amendment_queued, etc.)\n- Durable payload records (plan, implementation, QA results, etc.) with cycle/attempt tracking\n- Artifact records (rendered outputs, validations)\n- Rollback point metadata (last rollback ID, rollback count)\n- Amendment queue (pending modifications, processed count)\n- Session management for backend reuse\n\n**Daemon Infrastructure:**\n- Task records (pending, claimed, active, completed, failed, aborted states)\n- Worktree leases with heartbeat tracking\n- Task routing (source: CLI, API, Webhook, etc.)\n- Daemon journal (task lifecycle events)\n- Writer locks for project synchronization\n\n**Requirements Drafting:**\n- Requirements runs with draft/quick modes\n- Question sets with IDs, descriptions, and answer validation\n- Requirements drafts with findings and flow recommendations\n- Review outcomes (approved, requested_changes, rejected)\n- Project seed payloads (project.json, prompt.md)\n- Answer TOML files with validation\n\n### AGENT EXECUTION & BACKEND ABSTRACTION\n\n**Backend Family Support:**\n- Claude, Codex, OpenRouter, Stub (each with configurable model IDs)\n- Backend capabilities: structured output, session reuse, cancellation support\n- Stage-specific backend role mapping (Planner, Implementer, Reviewer, QaValidator, CompletionJudge)\n\n**Invocation Contract System:**\n- `InvocationContract` enum supporting both Stage contracts and Requirements contracts\n- Contract evaluation pipeline: JSON schema → domain validation → Markdown rendering\n- Capability checks before invocation\n- Timeout handling with configurable durations\n- Cancellation support with token-based abort\n- Session persistence and reuse tracking\n\n**StubBackendAdapter (testing):**\n- Deterministic canned payloads for all stages\n- Delay injection for latency testing\n- Transient failure simulation (fail N times, then succeed)\n- Per-stage and per-label payload overrides\n- Capability mismatch injection\n- Invocation failure injection\n- Cancellation tracking\n\n### REQUIREMENTS DRAFTING SYSTEM (Recently Added - Loop 10)\n\n**Four-Stage Interactive Flow:**\n1. **QuestionSet**: Backend generates questions based on user idea\n2. **RequirementsDraft**: Backend synthesizes requirements from user answers\n3. **RequirementsReview**: Backend or human reviews and approves/rejects\n4. **ProjectSeed**: Auto-generates project.json and prompt.md for `project create`\n\n**Service Operations:**\n- `draft`: Questions → answers → requirements (multi-round, user-driven)\n- `quick`: Questions → answers → requirements (automated, no human input)\n- `show`: Display requirements run status and details\n- `answer`: Submit user answers to pending questions (TOML format)\n\n**Contract Validation:**\n- Duplicate question ID detection\n- Empty required field detection\n- Flow preset validation\n- Finding requirement enforcement for non-approvals\n- Markdown rendering determinism\n\n### CONFORMANCE TEST SUITE\n\n**16 Gherkin Feature Files** with 100+ scenarios covering:\n\n1. **workspace_init.feature** - Workspace initialization and directory structure\n2. **workspace_config.feature** - Configuration management\n3. **active_project.feature** - Project selection and activation\n4. **project_records.feature** - Project CRUD operations\n5. **flow_discovery.feature** - Flow listing and details\n6. **stage_contracts.feature** - Contract validation pipelines\n7. **requirements_drafting.feature** (10 scenarios) - Complete requirements flow\n8. **run_queries.feature** - Status, history, tail queries\n9. **run_start_standard.feature** - Standard preset execution end-to-end\n10. **run_start_quick_dev.feature** - QuickDev preset execution\n11. **run_start_docs_change.feature** - DocsChange preset execution\n12. **run_start_ci_improvement.feature** - CiImprovement preset execution\n13. **run_completion_rounds.feature** - Completion panel refinement cycles\n14. **run_resume_retry.feature** - Resume from failed with retry\n15. **run_resume_non_standard.feature** - Resume across different flow types\n16. **daemon_lifecycle.feature** - Daemon start, status, abort, retry, reconcile\n17. **daemon_routing.feature** - Task routing and execution\n\n### WHAT'S NOT IMPLEMENTED\n\n1. **Conformance Command** (`conformance list`, `conformance run`) - Gherkin runner infrastructure\n2. **Run Rollback** - Stage rollback functionality (`run rollback --to <stage> --hard`)\n3. **Real Backend Drivers** - Only stub adapter; Claude/Codex/OpenRouter adapters would need actual API clients\n4. **Conformance Specification Context** - Module exists but contains no code (placeholder)\n5. **Answer Validation** - Permissive TOML parsing (doesn't enforce required-question coverage)\n\n### KEY DESIGN PATTERNS\n\n1. **Port-Adapter Architecture** - All external dependencies (fs, git, backends) are traits\n2. **Domain Contracts** - JSON schema → domain validation → markdown rendering pipeline\n3. **Deterministic Testing** - StubBackendAdapter enables test reproducibility\n4. **Error Classification** - `FailureClass` enum (TransportFailure, SchemaValidationFailure, DomainValidationFailure, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailure) drives retry semantics\n5. **Durable Atomicity** - FileSystem uses atomic writes with temp files and rename\n6. **NDJSON Journals** - Append-only event journals for durability\n7. **Remediation Semantics** - Configurable retry policies, cycle limits, completion rounds\n\n### TEST COVERAGE\n\n- **Unit Tests**: 319 passing tests across domains (domain, flow, stage contracts, agent execution, requirements, daemon models)\n- **CLI Tests**: 84 integration tests exercising all commands\n- **Conformance**: 100+ Gherkin scenarios (feature files defined, runner not yet implemented)\n\n### FILES STRUCTURE\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── main.rs (20 lines) - Entry point\n├── lib.rs (7 lines) - Module declarations\n├── cli/\n│   ├── mod.rs - Command routing\n│   ├── init.rs - Workspace initialization\n│   ├── flow.rs - Flow discovery\n│   ├── config.rs - Workspace config\n│   ├── project.rs - Project management\n│   ├── run.rs - Run execution (start, resume, status, history, tail)\n│   ├── requirements.rs - Requirements drafting\n│   ├── daemon.rs - Daemon lifecycle\n│   └── conformance.rs - Conformance (NOT IMPLEMENTED)\n├── contexts/\n│   ├── workspace_governance/ - Workspace config, active project tracking\n│   ├── project_run_record/ - Projects, runs, journals, artifacts, queries\n│   ├── workflow_composition/ - Stages, flows, contracts, engine (2295 lines)\n│   ├── agent_execution/ - Backend abstraction, invocation contracts\n│   ├── requirements_drafting/ - Requirements service (1197 lines in service alone)\n│   ├── automation_runtime/ - Daemon tasks, leases, routing\n│   └── conformance_spec/ - Placeholder\n├── adapters/\n│   ├── fs.rs - Filesystem persistence\n│   ├── stub_backend.rs - Testing mock\n│   └── worktree.rs - Git worktree management\n└── shared/\n    ├── domain.rs - Core domain types (663 lines)\n    └── error.rs - Error types with failure classification\n```\n\n### RECENT PROGRESS (Loop 12)\n\nBased on git commits and implementation notes, the most recent work focused on:\n- Adding support for all four flow presets in run start\n- Implementing requirements drafting service with interactive question/answer flow\n- Extending agent execution to support non-stage contracts (requirements)\n- Comprehensive daemon lifecycle support (start, status, abort, retry, reconcile)\n\n### READY TO BUILD\n\nThe codebase is **highly complete** with clear TODOs only for:\n1. Conformance test runner (feature files exist, harness missing)\n2. Run rollback implementation\n3. Real backend adapters (would require external API clients)\n\nAll core domain logic, workflows, persistence, error handling, and testing infrastructure are production-quality."}],"totalDurationMs":75224,"totalTokens":68098,"totalToolUseCount":43,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2118,"cache_read_input_tokens":62978,"output_tokens":3002,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2118},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
