{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NB5bds4zjbrU4SsLwi4UTt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Retry, Remediation, and Resume\n     2→  Standard-flow runs retry retryable stage failures, pause for prompt-review\n     3→  revision, loop through remediation cycles when QA or review request\n     4→  changes, and resume only from durable stage boundaries.\n     5→\n     6→  # SC-RESUME-001\n     7→  Scenario: Retryable implementation failure succeeds on the second attempt\n     8→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n     9→    And project \"alpha\" is selected as active\n    10→    And the implementation stage will fail once with a transport failure\n    11→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    12→    Then the command exits successfully\n    13→    And the journal contains a \"stage_failed\" event for \"implementation\" with attempt 1 and will_retry true\n    14→    And the journal contains a second \"stage_entered\" event for \"implementation\" with attempt 2\n    15→    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    16→\n    17→  # SC-RESUME-002\n    18→  Scenario: Retry exhaustion fails the run and clears the active cursor\n    19→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"bravo\" using flow \"standard\"\n    20→    And project \"bravo\" is selected as active\n    21→    And the implementation stage will fail for all retry attempts with a transport failure\n    22→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    23→    Then the command fails with error containing \"implementation\"\n    24→    And the journal ends with a \"run_failed\" event referencing \"implementation\"\n    25→    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n    26→\n    27→  # SC-RESUME-003\n    28→  Scenario: QA request_changes advances the cycle and reruns implementation\n    29→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"charlie\" using flow \"standard\"\n    30→    And project \"charlie\" is selected as active\n    31→    And the QA stage returns \"request_changes\" with follow-up amendment \"add missing regression test\"\n    32→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    33→    Then the command exits successfully\n    34→    And the journal contains a \"cycle_advanced\" event from cycle 1 to cycle 2 resuming at \"implementation\"\n    35→    And the implementation stage is entered twice across the run\n    36→    And the second implementation invocation includes the QA follow-up amendment in its remediation context\n    37→\n    38→  # SC-RESUME-004\n    39→  Scenario: Prompt review not ready pauses the run for revision\n    40→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"delta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    41→    And project \"delta\" is selected as active\n    42→    And the prompt_review stage returns readiness.ready false\n    43→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    44→    Then the command exits successfully\n    45→    And the run snapshot shows status \"paused\" with no active run\n    46→    And the status summary instructs the user to revise the prompt and run \"run resume\"\n    47→    And the prompt_review payload and artifact are persisted before the pause\n    48→\n    49→  # SC-RESUME-005\n    50→  Scenario: Run resume continues a failed run from the first incomplete durable stage\n    51→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"echo\" using flow \"standard\"\n    52→    And project \"echo\" is selected as active\n    53→    And a previous \"run start\" failed after planning completed and implementation exhausted retries\n    54→    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    55→    Then the command exits successfully\n    56→    And the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n    57→    And the planning stage is not re-executed\n    58→    And the first resumed stage is \"implementation\" with attempt 1\n    59→\n    60→  # SC-RESUME-006\n    61→  Scenario: Run resume continues a paused prompt-review run from planning\n    62→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"foxtrot\" using flow \"standard\"\n    63→    And project \"foxtrot\" is selected as active\n    64→    And a previous \"run start\" paused after \"prompt_review\" with readiness.ready false\n    65→    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    66→    Then the command exits successfully\n    67→    And the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n    68→    And the first resumed stage is \"planning\" with attempt 1\n    69→    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    70→\n    71→  # SC-RESUME-007\n    72→  Scenario: Run resume rejects non-resumable snapshot statuses\n    73→    Given initialized workspace projects with standard-flow snapshots in statuses \"not_started\", \"running\", and \"completed\"\n    74→    When the user runs \"run resume\" for each project\n    75→    Then each command fails with a clear status-specific error\n    76→    And none of the commands mutate canonical run state\n    77→\n    78→  # SC-RESUME-008\n    79→  Scenario: Run start rejects failed or paused snapshots and directs the user to resume\n    80→    Given initialized workspace projects with standard-flow snapshots in statuses \"failed\" and \"paused\"\n    81→    When the user runs \"run start\" for each project\n    82→    Then each command fails with error containing \"run resume\"\n    83→    And no new run_id is created for either project\n    84→\n    85→  # SC-RESUME-009\n    86→  Scenario: Cancellation during a retry loop halts further retries immediately\n    87→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"golf\" using flow \"standard\"\n    88→    And project \"golf\" is selected as active\n    89→    And the implementation stage is cancelled during its first retryable failure\n    90→    When the engine handles the failure\n    91→    Then no further \"stage_entered\" events are emitted for \"implementation\"\n    92→    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n    93→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9efe3b3c-046c-49b6-b72a-68be6f4e5436","uuid":"7b4e40b1-a2a0-4e8b-ba7e-98e34082fa88","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_resume_retry.feature","content":"Feature: Retry, Remediation, and Resume\n  Standard-flow runs retry retryable stage failures, pause for prompt-review\n  revision, loop through remediation cycles when QA or review request\n  changes, and resume only from durable stage boundaries.\n\n  # SC-RESUME-001\n  Scenario: Retryable implementation failure succeeds on the second attempt\n    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    And project \"alpha\" is selected as active\n    And the implementation stage will fail once with a transport failure\n    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    Then the command exits successfully\n    And the journal contains a \"stage_failed\" event for \"implementation\" with attempt 1 and will_retry true\n    And the journal contains a second \"stage_entered\" event for \"implementation\" with attempt 2\n    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n\n  # SC-RESUME-002\n  Scenario: Retry exhaustion fails the run and clears the active cursor\n    Given an initialized workspace with project \"bravo\" using flow \"standard\"\n    And project \"bravo\" is selected as active\n    And the implementation stage will fail for all retry attempts with a transport failure\n    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    Then the command fails with error containing \"implementation\"\n    And the journal ends with a \"run_failed\" event referencing \"implementation\"\n    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n\n  # SC-RESUME-003\n  Scenario: QA request_changes advances the cycle and reruns implementation\n    Given an initialized workspace with project \"charlie\" using flow \"standard\"\n    And project \"charlie\" is selected as active\n    And the QA stage returns \"request_changes\" with follow-up amendment \"add missing regression test\"\n    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    Then the command exits successfully\n    And the journal contains a \"cycle_advanced\" event from cycle 1 to cycle 2 resuming at \"implementation\"\n    And the implementation stage is entered twice across the run\n    And the second implementation invocation includes the QA follow-up amendment in its remediation context\n\n  # SC-RESUME-004\n  Scenario: Prompt review not ready pauses the run for revision\n    Given an initialized workspace with project \"delta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    And project \"delta\" is selected as active\n    And the prompt_review stage returns readiness.ready false\n    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    Then the command exits successfully\n    And the run snapshot shows status \"paused\" with no active run\n    And the status summary instructs the user to revise the prompt and run \"run resume\"\n    And the prompt_review payload and artifact are persisted before the pause\n\n  # SC-RESUME-005\n  Scenario: Run resume continues a failed run from the first incomplete durable stage\n    Given an initialized workspace with project \"echo\" using flow \"standard\"\n    And project \"echo\" is selected as active\n    And a previous \"run start\" failed after planning completed and implementation exhausted retries\n    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    Then the command exits successfully\n    And the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n    And the planning stage is not re-executed\n    And the first resumed stage is \"implementation\" with attempt 1\n\n  # SC-RESUME-006\n  Scenario: Run resume continues a paused prompt-review run from planning\n    Given an initialized workspace with project \"foxtrot\" using flow \"standard\"\n    And project \"foxtrot\" is selected as active\n    And a previous \"run start\" paused after \"prompt_review\" with readiness.ready false\n    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    Then the command exits successfully\n    And the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n    And the first resumed stage is \"planning\" with attempt 1\n    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n\n  # SC-RESUME-007\n  Scenario: Run resume rejects non-resumable snapshot statuses\n    Given initialized workspace projects with standard-flow snapshots in statuses \"not_started\", \"running\", and \"completed\"\n    When the user runs \"run resume\" for each project\n    Then each command fails with a clear status-specific error\n    And none of the commands mutate canonical run state\n\n  # SC-RESUME-008\n  Scenario: Run start rejects failed or paused snapshots and directs the user to resume\n    Given initialized workspace projects with standard-flow snapshots in statuses \"failed\" and \"paused\"\n    When the user runs \"run start\" for each project\n    Then each command fails with error containing \"run resume\"\n    And no new run_id is created for either project\n\n  # SC-RESUME-009\n  Scenario: Cancellation during a retry loop halts further retries immediately\n    Given an initialized workspace with project \"golf\" using flow \"standard\"\n    And project \"golf\" is selected as active\n    And the implementation stage is cancelled during its first retryable failure\n    When the engine handles the failure\n    Then no further \"stage_entered\" events are emitted for \"implementation\"\n    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n","numLines":93,"startLine":1,"totalLines":93}}}
